Program: Outlook
Title: Turkish Writer Perihan Mağden
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbryv
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Turkish writer Perihan Mağden talks about conscientious objection and censorship in Turkey; Can the architecture of your house make you happy? Rise of Islam in Togo and the resulting drop in numbers of girls attending school. Listeners report on evidence of global warming. Presenter: Heather Payton.